uk.ac.ebi.gxa.loader.utils
Class SDRFWritingUtils

java.lang.Object
  uk.ac.ebi.gxa.loader.utils.SDRFWritingUtils

public class SDRFWritingUtils
extends Object

A class filled with handy convenience methods for performing writing tasks common to lots of SDRF graph nodes. This class contains methods that hepl with writing Property objects out given some nodes in the SDRF graph.

Author:
Tony Burdett

writeSampleProperties

public static void writeSampleProperties(uk.ac.ebi.arrayexpress2.magetab.datamodel.MAGETABInvestigation investigation,
                                         Sample sample,
                                         uk.ac.ebi.arrayexpress2.magetab.datamodel.sdrf.node.SourceNode sourceNode)
                                  throws uk.ac.ebi.arrayexpress2.magetab.exception.ObjectConversionException
Write out the properties associated with a Sample in the SDRF graph. These properties are obtained by looking at the "characteristic" column in the SDRF graph, extracting the type and linking this type (the property) to the name of the SourceNode provided (the property value).

Parameters:
investigation - the investigation being loaded
sample - the sample you want to attach properties to
sourceNode - the sourceNode being read
Throws:
uk.ac.ebi.arrayexpress2.magetab.exception.ObjectConversionException - if there is a problem creating the property object
